In addition to maintaining power, they are also involved in various criminal activities such as Bank heists, Kidnappings, Extortion, Money laundering, Arms trafficking, Drug manufacturing and Smuggling, Fraud, Arson, Vandalism, Gang wars, illegal racing, and Fake Police.

title: Lower Street
notes: Lower Street, Lower Street is an alley that operates in the center of the eastern city of Los Santos. Los Santos is a large city. It is a center of commerce, culture and entertainment, but it also has major problems of crime and social inequality. Lower Street Gang stems from the dissatisfaction and injustice felt by the residents of the residential areas along Lower Street. The city government, which tends to prioritize big business interests and elite areas, has ignored the problems faced by residents in this area. Their environment is getting worse, while economic opportunities are limited.

title: Roadmen
notes: Roadmen are a predominantly British gang currently operating in Los Santos. They are involved in criminal activities such as car upgrades, street racing, drug dealing, gang wars, robbery, gun manufacturing, arms trading and murder. Roadmen members also maintain a legal lifestyle and operate multiple business ventures throughout Los Santos. This gang, which often wears puffer jackets and necklaces, now has about 30 active members, including newcomers, usually called New Muscles, consisting of Asian, African and British natives who have migrated to Los Santos.

title: Scaletta Crime Family
notes: Italian Gang, or the Scaletta family, is an informal Mafia clan established in the early 1960s by Vito Scaletta when he was assigned by The Commission to join the Marcano family and help manage their lucrative rackets in New Bordeaux. Grudgingly accepted by Sal Marcano, who looked down on him as a ''dirty carpetbagger'', Vito opted to rely on his own muscle rather than use anyone loyal to the Marcanos. Although most of his associates had Italian blood, he also brought a number of Hispanic and black mobsters into his gang as well.

title: Silent
notes: Silent was formed on March 23, 2023, in the heart of the east side, The area was plagued by poverty, unemployment, and a lack of opportunities, making it a breeding ground for criminal activities. A group of young individuals, born and raised in this environment, came together to form a gang as a means of survival. in response to the growing economic and social challenges faced by the community. The founders believed that their neighborhood needed a collective effort to address these issues, even if it meant operating outside the boundaries of the law.
